President Obama held a briefing with FEMA Administrator Craig Fugate, National Hurricane Center Director Dr. Rick Knabb, and Homeland Security Advisor John Brennan to discuss Hurricane Sandy. The President directed FEMA to provide all available federal resources to support state and local responders along the eastern seaboard. FEMA is deploying teams to multiple states to assist with storm preparations, and is urging coordination between local authorities and utility companies to prepare for potential power outages. The President requested regular updates on weather forecasts and preparations.